{"parentUuid":"80b01a5e-d9b5-4215-b4a6-608a21f290a9","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"9823e89e-4a23-4ccc-9757-1b9bb393ba5c","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a312a3a","slug":"jolly-snuggling-giraffe","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KK2YanEFWo49MyjYpQ6WzN","type":"tool_result","content":"   359→### US-GTD-1: Capture to Inbox\n   360→\n   361→**As a** GTD practitioner,\n   362→**I want to** quickly capture anything on my mind into my inbox,\n   363→**So that** I can get it out of my head and process it later.\n   364→\n   365→#### Acceptance Criteria\n   366→\n   367→- [ ] Inbox capture input is always accessible (prominent on the main page, and available\n   368→  via a persistent capture input on every authenticated page)\n   369→- [ ] Capture is fast: type and press Enter, item appears in inbox\n   370→- [ ] No categorization required at capture time (that happens during clarify)\n   371→- [ ] Inbox items show in a list ordered by capture time (oldest first -- process in\n   372→  FIFO order, like a physical inbox)\n   373→- [ ] Inbox count is visible in the navigation so users know how many items need processing\n   374→- [ ] Input has a visible `<label>` and helpful placeholder text\n   375→- [ ] After capturing, the input field is cleared and focus returns to it\n   376→- [ ] Empty or whitespace-only submissions are silently ignored\n   377→- [ ] Title has a maximum length of 300 characters\n   378→- [ ] Works without JavaScript (full page reload); HTMX enhances\n   379→- [ ] `aria-live` region announces \"Captured to inbox\" after HTMX swap\n   380→- [ ] Capture event is logged with structured tracing\n   381→\n   382→#### Accessibility\n   383→- [ ] All interactive elements are fully keyboard operable\n   384→- [ ] Capture input has a visible `<label>` associated via `for`/`id`\n   385→- [ ] Focus management: after capture, focus returns to the input\n   386→- [ ] Skip link bypasses header capture input to reach main content\n   387→- [ ] Screen reader announces inbox count change after capture\n   388→\n   389→#### Empty State\n   390→- When the inbox is empty, show: \"Inbox zero -- nothing to process. Capture something\n   391→  new or start your weekly review.\" with links to capture input and weekly review.\n   392→\n   393→#### Edge Cases\n   394→- Adding with only whitespace (silently ignored)\n   395→- Rapid successive captures\n   396→- Very long text (at or beyond max length)\n   397→- Special characters, HTML, emoji\n   398→"}]},"uuid":"945f1de8-d9ab-4fed-85ce-e4fd77e83e1f","timestamp":"2026-02-11T18:58:57.026Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list/docs/user-stories.md","content":"### US-GTD-1: Capture to Inbox\n\n**As a** GTD practitioner,\n**I want to** quickly capture anything on my mind into my inbox,\n**So that** I can get it out of my head and process it later.\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Inbox capture input is always accessible (prominent on the main page, and available\n  via a persistent capture input on every authenticated page)\n- [ ] Capture is fast: type and press Enter, item appears in inbox\n- [ ] No categorization required at capture time (that happens during clarify)\n- [ ] Inbox items show in a list ordered by capture time (oldest first -- process in\n  FIFO order, like a physical inbox)\n- [ ] Inbox count is visible in the navigation so users know how many items need processing\n- [ ] Input has a visible `<label>` and helpful placeholder text\n- [ ] After capturing, the input field is cleared and focus returns to it\n- [ ] Empty or whitespace-only submissions are silently ignored\n- [ ] Title has a maximum length of 300 characters\n- [ ] Works without JavaScript (full page reload); HTMX enhances\n- [ ] `aria-live` region announces \"Captured to inbox\" after HTMX swap\n- [ ] Capture event is logged with structured tracing\n\n#### Accessibility\n- [ ] All interactive elements are fully keyboard operable\n- [ ] Capture input has a visible `<label>` associated via `for`/`id`\n- [ ] Focus management: after capture, focus returns to the input\n- [ ] Skip link bypasses header capture input to reach main content\n- [ ] Screen reader announces inbox count change after capture\n\n#### Empty State\n- When the inbox is empty, show: \"Inbox zero -- nothing to process. Capture something\n  new or start your weekly review.\" with links to capture input and weekly review.\n\n#### Edge Cases\n- Adding with only whitespace (silently ignored)\n- Rapid successive captures\n- Very long text (at or beyond max length)\n- Special characters, HTML, emoji\n","numLines":40,"startLine":359,"totalLines":762}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"80b01a5e-d9b5-4215-b4a6-608a21f290a9"}
