   <li><a href=\"/waiting-for\"{% if current_page == \"waiting_for\" %} aria-current=\"page\"{% endif %} class=\"gtd-nav__link\">Waiting For</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/someday-maybe\"{% if current_page == \"someday_maybe\" %} aria-current=\"page\"{% endif %} class=\"gtd-nav__link\">Someday/Maybe</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/review\"{% if current_page == \"review\" %} aria-current=\"page\"{% endif %} class=\"gtd-nav__link\">Weekly Review</a></li>\n        </ul>\n    </nav>\n    <div class=\"gtd-header__actions\">\n        <form method=\"post\" action=\"/inbox\" class=\"quick-capture\" aria-label=\"Quick capture\">\n            <label for=\"quick-capture-title\" class=\"visually-hidden\">Quick capture</label>\n            <input\n                type=\"text\"\n                id=\"quick-capture-title\"\n                name=\"title\"\n                placeholder=\"Capture something...\"\n                maxlength=\"300\"\n                autocomplete=\"off\"\n                class=\"quick-capture__input\"\n            >\n            <button type=\"submit\" class=\"quick-capture__submit\">Capture</button>\n        </form>\n        <form method=\"post\" action=\"/logout\" class=\"nav-logout\" hx-boost=\"false\">\n            <button type=\"submit\" class=\"nav-logout__button\">Sign out</button>\n        </form>\n    </div>\n</div>\n","numLines":32,"startLine":1,"totalLines":32}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d54ac95f-8fc1-42ec-9bdc-8a1c68a85a35"}
{"parentUuid":"8eea5a1f-addb-41ad-be27-ec4ccc80e431","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"9823e89e-4a23-4ccc-9757-1b9bb393ba5c","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a312a3a","slug":"jolly-snuggling-giraffe","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Eod7TEJQhg865NfGmpgM2S","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the nav has already been updated with `inbox_count` and the quick capture form. The badge uses `aria-label` which Heydon recommended against -- it should be plain text in parentheses. Let me send Luca the inbox page design specs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":905,"cache_read_input_tokens":154332,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":905,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global","research_preview_2026_02":"active"}},"requestId":"req_011CY2o7MQhCN6XLkVR3TtQU","type":"assistant","uuid":"72aa7587-6ae4-4b89-9309-b9fb5a789a22","timestamp":"2026-02-11T18:59:29.178Z"}
{"parentUuid":"72aa7587-6ae4-4b89-9309-b9fb5a789a22","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"9823e89e-4a23-4ccc-9757-1b9bb393ba5c","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a312a3a","slug":"jolly-snuggling-giraffe","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Eod7TEJQhg865NfGmpgM2S","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Y8GZBUKDqtU7otFde5LgXT","name":"SendMessage","input":{"type":"message","recipient":"luca-palmieri","content":"Luca, here are the design specs for the Inbox Capture page (US-GTD-1).\n\n## Inbox Page Design Spec\n\n### Page Structure\n```\n[GTD Header Nav]\n\nInbox                              X items to process\n\n[Capture input: ____________________]  [Capture]\n\n- Item title (oldest)                  [Process]\n- Item title                           [Process]\n- Item title (newest)                  [Process]\n```\n\n### Components\n\n**Page header area:**\n- `<h1>` \"Inbox\"\n- Item count as muted text next to heading: \"X items to process\" in `--font-size-sm`, `--color-fg-muted`\n- When inbox is zero: no count text\n\n**Capture form (on the inbox page itself):**\n- This is the PRIMARY capture point -- more prominent than the header quick capture\n- Visible `<label>`: \"What's on your mind?\" -- `--font-size-sm`, `--font-medium`\n- Text input + \"Capture\" button in a row (same pattern as current `.todo-add__row`)\n- Placeholder: \"Capture anything -- you'll organize it later\"\n- After submit: input clears, focus returns to input, new item appears in list\n- HTMX: `hx-post=\"/inbox\"`, `hx-target` to prepend/append to the list (depends on sort order), `hx-on::after-request` to clear input on success\n\n**Inbox item list:**\n- Ordered by capture time -- **oldest first** (FIFO, per updated user story). The item at the top is the one to process next.\n- Each item is a simple row: title + capture timestamp + \"Process\" link\n- Use a `<ul role=\"list\">` like the todo list\n\n**Inbox item row:** `.inbox-item`\n```html\n<li class=\"inbox-item\">\n    <span class=\"inbox-item__title\">Call dentist about appointment</span>\n    <span class=\"inbox-item__time\">2 hours ago</span>\n    <a href=\"/inbox/{id}/clarify\" class=\"inbox-item__action\">Process</a>\n</li>\n```\n\nCSS specs:\n- `.inbox-item`: `display: flex`, `align-items: center`, `gap: var(--space-sm)`, `padding-block: var(--space-sm)`, `border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border)`\n- `.inbox-item:first-child`: `border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-border)` (same pattern as `.todo-item`)\n- `.inbox-item__title`: `flex: 1`, `min-inline-size: 0`, `overflow-wrap: break-word`\n- `.inbox-item__time`: `font-size: var(--font-size-xs)`, `color: var(--color-fg-subtle)`, `white-space: nowrap`, `flex-shrink: 0`\n- `.inbox-item__action`: `font-size: var(--font-size-sm)`, `color: var(--color-primary)`, `flex-shrink: 0`, `text-decoration: none` -- styled as a text link, not a button (it's navigation to the clarify page)\n- `.inbox-item__action:hover`: `text-decoration: underline`\n\n**Empty state:**\n- \"Inbox zero -- nothing to process.\" as the primary message\n- Below: \"Capture something new or start your weekly review.\" with \"weekly review\" as a link to `/review`\n- Use the existing `.todo-empty` pattern: `--color-fg-muted`, `--font-size-sm`, `text-align: center`, `padding-block: var(--space-xl)`\n\n**Delete action:**\n- Each inbox item should also have a delete/trash option (small, muted, secondary to \"Process\")\n- For the skeleton, \"Process\" link is sufficient. Delete can come with the clarify workflow since \"Trash\" is one of the clarify outcomes.\n\n### Nav Badge Fix\n\nI noticed in the updated `gtd_nav.html` that the inbox count uses `aria-label` on a `<span>`:\n```html\n<span class=\"gtd-nav__badge\" aria-label=\"({{ inbox_count }} items to process)\">{{ inbox_count }}</span>\n```\n\nPer Heydon's guidance, this should be **plain text in parentheses**, not `aria-label`:\n```html\nInbox <span class=\"nav-count\">({{ inbox_count }})</span>\n```\n\nThe `aria-label` on a `<span>` that isn't interactive may not be reliably announced. Plain text is simpler and guaranteed to work. The `<span class=\"nav-count\">` gives CSS control (smaller font, muted color). Screen readers read \"Inbox (3), link\" which matches what sighted users see.\n\nCSS for `.nav-count`:\n```css\n.nav-count {\n    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);\n    color: var(--color-fg-muted);\n}\n```\n\n### HTMX Enhancement\n\nFor the on-page capture form:\n- `hx-post=\"/inbox\"` on the form\n- `hx-target=\".inbox-list\"` targeting the list\n- `hx-swap=\"afterbegin\"` or `beforeend\"` depending on sort order (oldest first means new items go at the end: `beforeend`)\n- `hx-on::after-request=\"if(event.detail.successful) this.reset()\"` to clear the input\n- Response should include `HX-Trigger: {\"announce\": {\"value\": \"Captured to inbox\"}}` for the aria-live region\n\nFor the quick capture in the header (on non-inbox pages):\n- Same HTMX attributes but the response just confirms capture\n- The user doesn't see the item appear (they're on a different page) -- the aria-live announcement is the only feedback\n- The nav inbox count should update too -- this might need an `HX-Trigger` that refreshes the nav count, or the HTMX response can include an out-of-band swap for the nav badge\n\nLet me know if you need anything clarified.","summary":"Design specs for Inbox Capture page and nav badge fix"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":905,"cache_read_input_tokens":154332,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":905,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global","research_preview_2026_02":"active"}},"requestId":"req_011CY2o7MQhCN6XLkVR3TtQU","type":"assistant","uuid":"22f23db0-2611-49d3-a9e6-1826f0c07983","timestamp":"2026-02-11T18:59:40.822Z"}
{"parentUuid":"22f23db0-2611-49d3-a9e6-1826f0c07983","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"9823e89e-4a23-4ccc-9757-1b9bb393ba5c","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a312a3a","slug":"jolly-snuggling-giraffe","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y8GZBUKDqtU7otFde5LgXT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox\",\n  \"routing\": {\n    \"sender\": \"steve-schoger\",\n    \"senderColor\": \"cyan\",\n    \"target\": \"@luca-palmieri\",\n    \"targetColor\": \"purple\",\n    \"summary\": \"Design specs for Inbox Capture page and nav badge fix\",\n    \"content\": \"Luca, here are the design specs for the Inbox Capture page (US-GTD-1).\\n\\n## Inbox Page Design Spec\\n\\n### Page Structure\\n```\\n[GTD Header Nav]\\n\\nInbox                              X items to process\\n\\n[Capture input: ____________________]  [Capture]\\n\\n- Item title (oldest)                  [Process]\\n- Item title                           [Process]\\n- Item title (newest)                  [Process]\\n```\\n\\n### Components\\n\\n**Page header area:**\\n- `<h1>` \\\"Inbox\\\"\\n- Item count as muted text next to heading: \\\"X items to process\\\" in `--font-size-sm`, `--color-fg-muted`\\n- When inbox is zero: no count text\\n\\n**Capture form (on the inbox page itself):**\\n- This is the PRIMARY capture point -- more prominent than the header quick capture\\n- Visible `<label>`: \\\"What's on your mind?\\\" -- `--font-size-sm`, `--font-medium`\\n- Text input + \\\"Capture\\\" button in a row (same pattern as current `.todo-add__row`)\\n- Placeholder: \\\"Capture anything -- you'll organize it later\\\"\\n- After submit: input clears, focus returns to input, new item appears in list\\n- HTMX: `hx-post=\\\"/inbox\\\"`, `hx-target` to prepend/append to the list (depends on sort order), `hx-on::after-request` to clear input on success\\n\\n**Inbox item list:**\\n- Ordered by capture time -- **oldest first** (FIFO, per updated user story). The item at the top is the one to process next.\\n- Each item is a simple row: title + capture timestamp + \\\"Process\\\" link\\n- Use a `<ul role=\\\"list\\\">` like the todo list\\n\\n**Inbox item row:** `.inbox-item`\\n```html\\n<li class=\\\"inbox-item\\\">\\n    <span class=\\\"inbox-item__title\\\">Call dentist about appointment</span>\\n    <span class=\\\"inbox-item__time\\\">2 hours ago</span>\\n    <a href=\\\"/inbox/{id}/clarify\\\" class=\\\"inbox-item__action\\\">Process</a>\\n</li>\\n```\\n\\nCSS specs:\\n- `.inbox-item`: `display: flex`, `align-items: center`, `gap: var(--space-sm)`, `padding-block: var(--space-sm)`, `border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border)`\\n- `.inbox-item:first-child`: `border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-border)` (same pattern as `.todo-item`)\\n- `.inbox-item__title`: `flex: 1`, `min-inline-size: 0`, `overflow-wrap: break-word`\\n- `.inbox-item__time`: `font-size: var(--font-size-xs)`, `color: var(--color-fg-subtle)`, `white-space: nowrap`, `flex-shrink: 0`\\n- `.inbox-item__action`: `font-size: var(--font-size-sm)`, `color: var(--color-primary)`, `flex-shrink: 0`, `text-decoration: none` -- styled as a text link, not a button (it's navigation to the clarify page)\\n- `.inbox-item__action:hover`: `text-decoration: underline`\\n\\n**Empty state:**\\n- \\\"Inbox zero -- nothing to process.\\\" as the primary message\\n- Below: \\\"Capture something new or start your weekly review.\\\" with \\\"weekly review\\\" as a link to `/review`\\n- Use the existing `.todo-empty` pattern: `--color-fg-muted`, `--font-size-sm`, `text-align: center`, `padding-block: var(--space-xl)`\\n\\n**Delete action:**\\n- Each inbox item should also have a delete/trash option (small, muted, secondary to \\\"Process\\\")\\n- For the skeleton, \\\"Process\\\" link is sufficient. Delete can come with the clarify workflow since \\\"Trash\\\" is one of the clarify outcomes.\\n\\n### Nav Badge Fix\\n\\nI noticed in the updated `gtd_nav.html` that the inbox count uses `aria-label` on a `<span>`:\\n```html\\n<span class=\\\"gtd-nav__badge\\\" aria-label=\\\"({{ inbox_count }} items to process)\\\">{{ inbox_count }}</span>\\n```\\n\\nPer Heydon's guidance, this should be **plain text in parentheses**, not `aria-label`:\\n```html\\nInbox <span class=\\\"nav-count\\\">({{ inbox_count }})</span>\\n```\\n\\nThe `aria-label` on a `<span>` that isn't interactive may not be reliably announced. Plain text is simpler and guaranteed to work. The `<span class=\\\"nav-count\\\">` gives CSS control (smaller font, muted color). Screen readers read \\\"Inbox (3), link\\\" which matches what sighted users see.\\n\\nCSS for `.nav-count`:\\n```css\\n.nav-count {\\n    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);\\n    color: var(--color-fg-muted);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### HTMX Enhancement\\n\\nFor the on-page capture form:\\n- `hx-post=\\\"/inbox\\\"` on the form\\n- `hx-target=\\\".inbox-list\\\"` targeting the list\\n- `hx-swap=\\\"afterbegin\\\"` or `beforeend\\\"` depending on sort order (oldest first means new items go at the end: `beforeend`)\\n- `hx-on::after-request=\\\"if(event.detail.successful) this.reset()\\\"` to clear the input\\n- Response should include `HX-Trigger: {\\\"announce\\\": {\\\"value\\\": \\\"Captured to inbox\\\"}}` for the aria-live region\\n\\nFor the quick capture in the header (on non-inbox pages):\\n- Same HTMX attributes but the response just confirms capture\\n- The user doesn't see the item appear (they're on a different page) -- the aria-live announcement is the only feedback\\n- The nav inbox count should update too -- this might need an `HX-Trigger` that refreshes the nav count, or the HTMX response can include an out-of-band swap for the nav badge\\n\\nLet me know if you need anything clarified.\"\n  }\n}"}]}]},"uuid":"8d9abe51-ece0-463a-9ea3-3170ca5d5f2d","timestamp":"2026-02-11T18:59:40.834Z","toolUseResult":{"success":true,"message":"Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox","routing":{"sender":"steve-schoger","senderColor":"cyan","target":"@luca-palmieri","targetColor":"purple","summary":"Design specs for Inbox Capture page and nav badge fix","content":"Luca, here are the design specs for the Inbox Capture page (US-GTD-1).\n\n## Inbox Page Design Spec\n\n### Page Structure\n```\n[GTD Header Nav]\n\nInbox                              X items to process\n\n[Capture input: ____________________]  [Capture]\n\n- Item title (oldest)                  [Process]\n- Item title                           [Process]\n- Item title (newest)                  [Process]\n```\n\n### Components\n\n**Page header area:**\n- `<h1>` \"Inbox\"\n- Item count as muted text next to heading: \"X items to process\" in `--font-size-sm`, `--color-fg-muted`\n- When inbox is zero: no count text\n\n**Capture form (on the inbox page itself):**\n- This is the PRIMARY capture point -- more prominent than the header quick capture\n- Visible `<label>`: \"What's on your mind?\" -- `--font-size-sm`, `--font-medium`\n- Text input + \"Capture\" button in a row (same pattern as current `.todo-add__row`)\n- Placeholder: \"Capture anything -- you'll organize it later\"\n- After submit: input clears, focus returns to input, new item appears in list\n- HTMX: `hx-post=\"/inbox\"`, `hx-target` to prepend/append to the list (depends on sort order), `hx-on::after-request` to clear input on success\n\n**Inbox item list:**\n- Ordered by capture time -- **oldest first** (FIFO, per updated user story). The item at the top is the one to process next.\n- Each item is a simple row: title + capture timestamp + \"Process\" link\n- Use a `<ul role=\"list\">` like the todo list\n\n**Inbox item row:** `.inbox-item`\n```html\n<li class=\"inbox-item\">\n    <span class=\"inbox-item__title\">Call dentist about appointment</span>\n    <span class=\"inbox-item__time\">2 hours ago</span>\n    <a href=\"/inbox/{id}/clarify\" class=\"inbox-item__action\">Process</a>\n</li>\n```\n\nCSS specs:\n- `.inbox-item`: `display: flex`, `align-items: center`, `gap: var(--space-sm)`, `padding-block: var(--space-sm)`, `border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border)`\n- `.inbox-item:first-child`: `border-block-start: 1px solid var(--color-border)` (same pattern as `.todo-item`)\n- `.inbox-item__title`: `flex: 1`, `min-inline-size: 0`, `overflow-wrap: break-word`\n- `.inbox-item__time`: `font-size: var(--font-size-xs)`, `color: var(--color-fg-subtle)`, `white-space: nowrap`, `flex-shrink: 0`\n- `.inbox-item__action`: `font-size: var(--font-size-sm)`, `color: var(--color-primary)`, `flex-shrink: 0`, `text-decoration: none` -- styled as a text link, not a button (it's navigation to the clarify page)\n- `.inbox-item__action:hover`: `text-decoration: underline`\n\n**Empty state:**\n- \"Inbox zero -- nothing to process.\" as the primary message\n- Below: \"Capture something new or start your weekly review.\" with \"weekly review\" as a link to `/review`\n- Use the existing `.todo-empty` pattern: `--color-fg-muted`, `--font-size-sm`, `text-align: center`, `padding-block: var(--space-xl)`\n\n**Delete action:**\n- Each inbox item should also have a delete/trash option (small, muted, secondary to \"Process\")\n- For the skeleton, \"Process\" link is sufficient. Delete can come with the clarify workflow since \"Trash\" is one of the clarify outcomes.\n\n### Nav Badge Fix\n\nI noticed in the updated `gtd_nav.html` that the inbox count uses `aria-label` on a `<span>`:\n```html\n<span class=\"gtd-nav__badge\" aria-label=\"({{ inbox_count }} items to process)\">{{ inbox_count }}</span>\n```\n\nPer Heydon's guidance, this should be **plain text in parentheses**, not `aria-label`:\n```html\nInbox <span class=\"nav-count\">({{ inbox_count }})</span>\n```\n\nThe `aria-label` on a `<span>` that isn't interactive may not be reliably announced. Plain text is simpler and guaranteed to work. The `<span class=\"nav-count\">` gives CSS control (smaller font, muted color). Screen readers read \"Inbox (3), link\" which matches what sighted users see.\n\nCSS for `.nav-count`:\n```css\n.nav-count {\n    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);\n    color: var(--color-fg-muted);\n}\n```\n\n### HTMX Enhancement\n\nFor the on-page capture form:\n- `hx-post=\"/inbox\"` on the form\n- `hx-target=\".inbox-list\"` targeting the list\n- `hx-swap=\"afterbegin\"` or `beforeend\"` depending on sort order (oldest first means new items go at the end: `beforeend`)\n- `hx-on::after-request=\"if(event.detail.successful) this.reset()\"` to clear the input\n- Response should include `HX-Trigger: {\"announce\": {\"value\": \"Captured to inbox\"}}` for the aria-live region\n\nFor the quick capture in the header (on non-inbox pages):\n- Same HTMX attributes but the response just confirms capture\n- The user doesn't see the item appear (they're on a different page) -- the aria-live announcement is the only feedback\n- The nav inbox count should update too -- this might need an `HX-Trigger` that refreshes the nav count, or the HTMX response can include an out-of-band swap for the nav badge\n\nLet me know if you need anything clarified."}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"22f23db0-2611-49d3-a9e6-1826f0c07983"}
